main event: Two civilian objects, described as round, shiny, and silver, appeared to remain stationary for 7 minutes in Glenwood, Iowa on August 11, 1955.
interesting points: The objects were seen through binoculars by civilian witnesses.
The duration of the sighting and the stationary nature of the objects suggested the possibility that they were balloons.
A previous similar sighting of a balloon was definitely identified as such.
No photographs were taken of the objects.
The report was part of Project Blue Book, the U.S. Air Force's investigation of UFO sightings.
